\c 18
\s1 Tugas para Imam dan Suku Lewi
\p
\v 1 TUHAN berkata kepada Harun, “Engkau dan anak-anak lelakimu beserta dengan keluarga ayahmu yang bertanggung jawab terhadap Kemah Suci. Tetapi hanya engkau dan anak-anakmu yang bertanggung jawab terhadap pekerjaan Imam.
\v 2 Haruslah mereka yang berasal dari suku Lewi, membantu engkau dan anak-anakmu ketika kalian melakukan tugas kalian di Kemah Suci.
\v 3 Namun sementara mereka melakukan pekerjaan mereka, tidaklah mereka boleh mendekat kepada barang-barang kudus yang ada di dalam kemah atau yang ada di dekat mezbah. Jika mereka melakukannya, mereka dan kalian juga akan mati!
\v 4 Haruslah mereka membantu kalian melakukan pekerjaan mengurus Kemah Suci, tetapi tidak seorangpun diijinkan mendekati tempat dimana kalian bekerja.
\p
\v 5 Kalianlah yang akan mengerjakan segala pekerjaan yang kudus di dalam Kemah Suci dan di mezbah. Jika kalian menaati perintah-perintah yang diberikan, Aku tidak akan pernah penuh murka dengan orang Israel lagi.
\v 6 Aku sendiri yang sudah memilih keturunan Lewi dari antara suku Israel lainnya sebagai hadiah untuk menjadi penolong bagi kalian dalam melakukan pekerjaan kudus di Kemah Suci.
\v 7 Tetapi hanya engkau dan anak-anakmu, sebagai para imam, yang harus melakukan semua tata cara keagamaan yang berhubungan dengan mezbah dan dengan semua yang terjadi di dalam tempat yang Maha Kudus. Pelayananmu adalah hadiah dari-Ku, dan siapapun yang mencoba melakukannya haruslah dihukum mati.”
\s1 Bagian persembahan untuk para imam dan orang Lewi
\p
\v 8 TUHAN juga berkata kepada Harun, “Akulah yang mengurapi engkau untuk mengurus semua persembahan kudus yang rakyat Israel persembahkan kepada-Ku. Seluruh persembahan kudus yang orang Israel persembahkan kepada-Ku, Aku berikan kepada engkau dan anak-anakmu. Engkau dan keturunanmu akan selalu mendapat bagian dari persembahan-persembahan ini selamanya.
\v 9 Bagian dari persembahan yang tidak terbakar habis di mezbah menjadi kepunyaan kalian. Bagian-bagian dari persembahan kudus, baik persembahan sajian, persembahan penebusan dosa dan persembahan penebusan kesalahan haruslah dipisahkan, dan diberikan kepada engkau dan anak-anakmu.
\v 10 Kalian haruslah makan persembahan itu di tempat kudus. Engkau dan setiap laki-laki dalam keluargamu boleh memakannya, persembahan itu kudus bagimu.
\p
\v 11 Seluruh persembahan yang dibawa oleh orang Israel kepada-Ku menjadi milik engkau dan anak-anak lelaki dan perempuanmu. Persembahan ini akan selalu menjadi bagian kalian. Setiap anggota keluargamu boleh memakannya bila mereka sudah menguduskan diri mereka di hadapan-Ku.
\p
\v 12 I am \add also\add* giving to you the first food that people harvest each year and bring to me—the best\add olive\add* oil and new wine and grain.
\v 13 All of the first crops that people harvest and bring to me belong to you. Anyone in your family who has\add performed the ritual to\add* become acceptable to me is permitted to eat that food.
\p
\v 14 Everything in Israel that is set apart to belong to me also belongs to you.
\v 15 The firstborn males, both humans and domestic animals, that are offered to me, will be yours. But people must buy back their firstborn sons and the firstborn animals that may not be used for sacrifices.
\v 16 They must buy them back when they are one month old. The price that they must pay\add for each one\add* is five pieces of silver. They must weigh the silver on the scales that are in the Sacred Tent.
\p
\v 17 But they are not permitted to buy back the firstborn cattle or sheep or goats. They are holy and have been set apart forme. \add Slaughter them and\add* sprinkle their blood on the altar. Then completely burn the fat of those animals\add on the altar\add* to be an offering to me. The smell as they burn will be very pleasing to me.
\v 18 The meat from those offerings will be yours, just like the breast and right thigh of animals that are presented to me to maintain fellowship with me as the priest lifts them up high in front of the altar are yours.
\v 19 Anything that the Israeli people present to me as holy/sacred gifts, I am giving to you. They are for you and your sonsand daughters \add to eat\add*. They will always be your share. This is an agreement that I am making with you, an agreement that will ◄last forever/never be changed►. I am also making this agreement with your descendants.”
\p
\v 20 Yahweh also said to Aaron, “You priests will not receive any of the land or the property like the\add other\add* Israeli people will receive. I am what you will receive.
\p
\v 21 When the Israeli people bring to me a tenth of all \add the crops and of their newbornanimals\add*, I will give that to you descendants of Levi. That will be your payment for the work you do at the Sacred Tent.
\v 22 The other Israelis must not go near that tent. If they go near it,\add I will consider that their doing that is a sin\add*, and they will die for committing that sin.
\v 23 Only the descendants of Levi are permitted to work at the Sacred Tent, and they will be punished if anything bad happens to it. That is a law that will never be changed. You descendants of Levi will not receive any land among the other Israeli people,
\v 24 because I will give you one tenth of all the \add crops andanimals\add* that the Israelis bring to be offerings to me. That is why I said that you will not receive any land like the other Israelis will receive.”
\p
\v 25 Yahweh said to Moses/me,
\v 26 “Tell this to the descendants of Levi: ‘When you receive one tenth of all\add the crops and animals\add* from the Israeli people, you must give one tenth of all that to me to be a sacred offering.
\v 27 Just like the other Israelis give one tenth of the grain and wine that they produce,
\v 28 you must give to me one tenth of all that you receive from them. That will be your sacred offering to me. You must present it to Aaron.
\v 29 Select the best parts of the things that are given to you to give them to me.’
\p
\v 30 Also, tell this to the descendants of Levi: ‘When you present those best portions of grain and wine as your offering to me, I will consider that those gifts are as though they came from your own grain and wine.
\v 31 You descendants of Levi and your families are permitted to eat\add the rest of\add* that food, and you may eat it wherever \add you wantto\add*, because it is your payment for the work that you do at the Sacred Tent.
\v 32 If you give to the priests the best portions of what you receive, you will not be punished\add by me\add* for accepting one tenth of the gifts that the people bring to me. But you must consider those gifts to besacred/holy. If you sin \add by eating those things in ways that are contrary to these regulations that I have given toyou\add*, you will be executed.’ ”